### Problem Description

The [reindex docs](https://www.elastic.co/docs/reference/elasticsearch/rest-apis/reindex-indices#reindex-remote-compatibility) correctly state that "Reindexing from remote clusters does not support manual or automatic slicing".

When you try to use automatic slicing (via the `slices` URL parameter) you correctly get an validation error e.g. "reindex from remote sources doesn't support slices > 1 but was [3]". (Aside: If you do `?slices=auto` you get "doesn't support slices > 1 but was [0]" which is a little weird, but this is only cosmetic.)

However, when you try to use manual slicing (via `source.slice` in the request body), it is silently ignored. You don't get any error. It just reindexes the whole index without doing any slicing.

This is clearly a bug. Assuming that we don't want to add support for manual slicing, the obvious fix would be to add the missing validation, although we need to pay attention to the backwards compatibility policy.

### Steps to Reproduce

Start an ES instance which whitelists reindex from itself, e.g.
```
./gradlew run -Dtests.es.reindex.remote.whitelist=localhost:9200
```
Create an index containing 10 documents:
```
PUT /original/_bulk?refresh
{"index":{}}
{"word": "one", "number": 1}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "two", "number": 2}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "three", "number": 3}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "four", "number": 4}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "five", "number": 5}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "six", "number": 6}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "seven", "number": 7}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "eight", "number": 8}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "nine", "number": 9}
{"index":{}}
{"word": "ten", "number": 10}
```
Reindex using the ES instance itself as a remote, manually specifying three slices with three destinations:
```
POST /_reindex
{
  "source": {
    "remote": {
      "host": "http://localhost:9200",
      "username": "elastic",
      "password": <PASSWORD>
    },
    "index": "original",
    "slice": {
      "id": 0,
      "max": 3
    }
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "remote-copy-0"
  }
}

POST /_reindex
{
  "source": {
    "remote": {
      "host": "http://localhost:9200",
      "username": "elastic",
      "password": <PASSWORD>
    },
    "index": "original",
    "slice": {
      "id": 1,
      "max": 3
    }
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "remote-copy-1"
  }
}

POST /_reindex
{
  "source": {
    "remote": {
      "host": "http://localhost:9200",
      "username": "elastic",
      "password": <PASSWORD>
    },
    "index": "original",
    "slice": {
      "id": 2,
      "max": 3
    }
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "remote-copy-2"
  }
}
```
Note that all three responses have `"total" : 10` and `"created" : 10`. Verify that all three destination indices contain all 10 documents:
```
GET /remote-copy-*/_stats

POST /remote-copy-0/_search

POST /remote-copy-1/_search

POST /remote-copy-2/_search
```

---

To prove that manual slicing works as expected when not reindexing from a remote cluster, do the equivalent local reindex operations:
```
POST /_reindex
{
  "source": {
    "index": "original",
    "slice": {
      "id": 0,
      "max": 3
    }
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "local-copy-0"
  }
}

POST /_reindex
{
  "source": {
    "index": "original",
    "slice": {
      "id": 1,
      "max": 3
    }
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "local-copy-1"
  }
}

POST /_reindex
{
  "source": {
    "index": "original",
    "slice": {
      "id": 2,
      "max": 3
    }
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "local-copy-2"
  }
}
```
Note that the responses have `"total"` values which sum to 10, e.g. 3, 2, and 5. Verify that the destination indices contain three different slices of the original index as expected:
```
GET /local-copy-*/_stats

POST /local-copy-0/_search

POST /local-copy-1/_search

POST /local-copy-2/_search
```

---
To verify that attempting to do automatic slicing fails validation as expected:
```
POST /_reindex?slices=3
{
  "source": {
    "remote": {
      "host": "http://localhost:9200",
      "username": "elastic",
      "password": <PASSWORD>
    },
    "index": "original"
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "fails"
  }
}

POST /_reindex?slices=auto
{
  "source": {
    "remote": {
      "host": "http://localhost:9200",
      "username": "elastic",
      "password": <PASSWORD>
    },
    "index": "original"
  },
  "dest": {
    "index": "fails"
  }
}
```

